// English Abstract


#text(lang:"en")[
  #set par(justify: true)

The abstract serves as a concise encapsulation of the entire document, spanning from a mere paragraph in papers to a more expansive half-page in the case of theses.
This section typically garners the initial attention of readers and often graces the forefront of search engine results summaries.

Prior to your final submission, crafting the abstract is likely one of your closing tasks.

It encompasses the following elements:
- *Motivation and Problem Statement*: This section sets the stage by outlining the driving factors and the challenges addressed within this work.
- *Approach*: Within this study, we have undertaken a comprehensive examination of both A and B, motivated by the rationale of C.
- *Results and Conclusion*: The paramount achievement lies in the discovery of D, which subsequently leads to the consequential outcome of E.


]
